description: Disables Allowed AMIs for your account in the specified Amazon Web Services Region. When set to disabled, the image criteria in your Allowed AMIs settings do not apply, and no restrictions are placed on AMI discoverability or usage. Users in your account can launch instances using any public AMI or AMI shared with your account. For more information, see Control the discovery and use of AMIs in Amazon EC2 with Allowed AMIs in Amazon EC2 User Guide.

nested_items.name: AllowedImagesSettingsState
nested_items.description: Returns disabled if the request succeeds; otherwise, it returns an error.
